<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/61401ATQDMVMSLPDTKCRQGQKNDHQSBBKR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Malika Tirolien";
  schema:description """
	Few artists command a stage with the power, versatility, and fearless creativity of Malika Tirolien. A GRAMMY-nominated singer, songwriter, producer, and composer, she has become one of the most distinctive voices in contemporary music, seamlessly weaving together jazz, soul, funk, Caribbean traditions, electronic music, and improvisation into a sound that is unmistakably her own.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Born in Guadeloupe and now based in Montréal, Malika first gained international recognition through her appearance on Snarky Puppy's acclaimed <span class=\"ItalicText\">Family Dinner – Volume One</span>, launching a career that has taken her to major concert halls and festivals around the world. She is also the celebrated lead vocalist of Bokanté, the internationally acclaimed ensemble founded by Michael League, whose album <span class=\"ItalicText\">What Heat</span> earned a GRAMMY nomination and introduced audiences worldwide to the band's rich blend of blues, Caribbean rhythms, West African influences, and jazz.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>As a solo artist, Malika continues to push creative boundaries while remaining deeply connected to her roots. Drawing inspiration from the Gwo Ka traditions of Guadeloupe alongside contemporary jazz, soul, and modern production, her music is both deeply personal and boldly innovative. Every performance is infused with extraordinary vocal command, emotional honesty, and an infectious sense of joy.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Whether delivering intimate moments of breathtaking vulnerability or unleashing explosive grooves with effortless virtuosity, Malika possesses the rare ability to make every performance feel both deeply personal and exhilarating. This is a rare opportunity to experience one of the most dynamic and captivating vocalists performing on the international stage today.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets: $30 Advance, $35 At the Door <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-28T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
